doc.after: Hispanic and Latino Americans are an ethnolinguistic group of Americans with origins in the countries of Latin America or the Iberian peninsula More generally it includes all persons in the United States who self identify as Hispanic or Latino Reflecting especially the Latin American population which has origins in all the continents and many ancestries Hispanic Latino Americans are very racially diverse and as a result form an ethnic category rather than a race
